article.headline: Baylor 75, Colorado 57
article.story: WACO, Texas -- Curtis Jerrells scored 29 and Baylor used a late run to beat Colorado 75-57 on Saturday. Colorado led 52-50 before a 3-pointer by Jerrells sparked the 23-5 run that put the game away. Jerrells scored 11 during the spurt. LaceDarius Dunn scored 10 for Baylor (17-11, 5-9 Big 12). Cory Higgins scored 20 and Dwight Thorne had 12 for Colorado (9-19, 1-13).
